<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="http://purl.org/olia/discourse/discourse.ISO.UDisc.owl#"
     xml:base="http://purl.org/olia/discourse/discourse.ISO.UDisc.owl"
     xmlns:iso="http://purl.org/olia/discourse/discourse.ISO.UDisc.owl#"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:skos="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#"
     xmlns:owl2xml="http://www.w3.org/2006/12/owl2-xml#">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://purl.org/olia/discourse/discourse.ISO.UDisc.owl">
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">ISO DR-Core (ISO 24617-8) adapted by Universal Discourse project: Core Concepts for the Annotation of Discourse Relations

The schema reuses the discourse.ISO.UDisc.owl from Discourse Extensions of the Ontologies of Linguistic Annotation (OLiA) by extending definitions:
- removing definition of an asymmetric argument role; Arg1 and Arg2 are represented as primitives and used also in symmetric relations to allow for discontinuities
- adding definition of a connective (with a label based on ISO 24617-8 definition from Section 3: Terms and definitions, definition 3.4: discourse connective, p. 2
- changing order of Cause arguments: for Result (to Arg1, was Arg2) and Reason (to Arg2, was Arg1)
- changing order of Condition arguments: for Consequent (to Arg1, was Arg2) and Antecedent (to Arg2, was Arg1)
- changing ID of Antecedent argument of Condition relation (was AntecedentOfCondition); the split to ConsequentOfCondition and ConsequentofNegativeCondition was preserved
- changing label of Negative Condition (was Consequent)
- changing order of Purpose arguments: for Enablement (to Arg1, was Arg2) and Goal (to Arg2, was Arg1)
- changing order of Manner arguments: for Achievement (to Arg1, was Arg2) and Means (to Arg2, was Arg1)
- changing ID of Regular argument of Exception relation (was RegularSituation)
- correcting label of Exemplification relation (was Excemplification)
- changing IDs of Broad and Specific arguments of Elaboration relation (were BroadPartOfElaboration and SpecificPartOfElaboration)
- changing Expansion arguments to Narrative (from Foreground) and Expander (from EntityDescription)
- adding object properties for each relation which enables instatiation
- updating relation definitions based on Table 1 from ISO 24617-8 (pp. 12–13)

References:
Harry Bunt and Rashmi Prasad (2012), ISO DR-Core (ISO 24617-8): Core Concepts for the Annotation of Discourse Relations, paper presented at ISA-12
ISO 24617-8:2016: Language resource management – Semantic annotation framework (SemAF) – Part 8: Semantic relations in discourse, core annotation schema (DR-core).
Maciej Ogrodniczuk and Dariusz Czerski (2026). Towards Corpus-Based Population and Visualization of ISO 24617-8 Ontology. In Proceedings of the 2026 Joint ACL – ISO Workshop on Interoperable Semantic Annotation (ISA-22) at LREC 2026. Palma de Mallorca, Spain. European Language Resources Association.

Funding information:
Funded in whole by the National Science Centre, Poland, grant 2023/50/A/HS2/00559 ('Universal Discourse: a multilingual model of discourse relations').</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Ontology>



